   9class Grib2Metadata():
  10    """
  11    Class to hold GRIB2 metadata both as numeric code value as stored in
  12    GRIB2 and its plain langauge definition.
  13
  14    **`value : int`**
  15
  16    GRIB2 metadata integer code value.
  17
  18    **`table : str, optional`**
  19
  20    GRIB2 table to lookup the `value`. Default is None.
  21    """
  22    __slots__ = ('definition','table','value')
  23    def __init__(self, value, table=None):
  24        self.value = value
  25        self.table = table
  26        if self.table is None:
  27            self.definition = None
  28        else:
  29            self.definition = tables.get_value_from_table(self.value,self.table)
  30    def __call__(self):
  31        return self.value
  32    def __repr__(self):
  33        return '%s(%d, table = %s)' % (self.__class__.__name__,self.value,self.table)
  34    def __str__(self):
  35        return '%d - %s' % (self.value,self.definition)
  36    def __eq__(self,other):
  37        return self.value == other
  38    def __gt__(self,other):
  39        return self.value > other
  40    def __ge__(self,other):
  41        return self.value >= other 
  42    def __lt__(self,other):
  43        return self.value < other
  44    def __le__(self,other):
  45        return self.value <= other
  46    def __contains__(self,other):
  47        return other in self.definition
  48
  49class Grib2Section:
  50    """Generic descriptor class for a GRIB2 section."""
  51    def __set_name__(self, owner, name):
  52        self.private_name = f'_{name}'
  53        
  54    def public_name(self):
  55        """Can be used by subclass with super().get_name() to discover
  56           the private name without _ ; helpfull for raising informative errors"""
  57        return self.private_name.strip('_')
  58        
  59    def __get__(self, obj, objtype=None):
  60        # Returning a copy prevents changes occuring to obj
  61        return copy(getattr(obj, self.private_name))
  62    
  63    def __set__(self, obj, value):
  64        # Logic for managing set
  65        print(f'setitem called on self.{self.public_name()}; rebuild Grib2msg Object')
  66        setattr(obj, self.private_name, value)

 168class RefDate:
 169    """Reference date as a `datetime.datetime` object"""
 170    def __get__(self, obj, objtype=None):
 171        return datetime.datetime(*obj._section1[5:11])
 172    def __set__(self, obj, value):
 173        if isinstance(value,datetime.datetime):
 174            obj._section1[5] = value.year
 175            obj._section1[6] = value.month
 176            obj._section1[7] = value.day
 177            obj._section1[8] = value.hour
 178            obj._section1[9] = value.minute
 179            obj._section1[10] = value.second
 180        else:
 181            msg = 'Reference date must be a datetime.datetime object.'
 182            raise TypeError(msg)

 231class EarthRadius:
 232    def __get__(self, obj, objtype=None):
 233        if obj._earthparams['shape'] == 'spherical':
 234            if obj._earthparams['radius'] is None:
 235                return obj._gridDefinitionTemplate[2]/(10.**obj._gridDefinitionTemplate[1])
 236            else:
 237                return obj._earthparams['radius']
 238        if obj._earthparams['shape'] == 'oblateSpheriod':
 239            if obj._earthparams['radius'] is None and obj._earthparams['major_axis'] is None and obj._earthparams['minor_axis'] is None:
 240                return obj._gridDefinitionTemplate[2]/(10.**obj._gridDefinitionTemplate[1])
 241            else:
 242                return earthparams['radius']
 243
 244class EarthMajorAxis:
 245    def __get__(self, obj, objtype=None):
 246        if obj._earthparams['shape'] == 'spherical':
 247            return None
 248        if obj._earthparams['shape'] == 'oblateSpheriod':
 249            if obj._earthparams['radius'] is None and obj._earthparams['major_axis'] is None and obj._earthparams['minor_axis'] is None:
 250                return obj._gridDefinitionTemplate[4]/(10.**obj._gridDefinitionTemplate[3])
 251            else:
 252                return earthparams['major_axis']
 253
 254class EarthMinorAxis:
 255    def __get__(self, obj, objtype=None):

 260                return obj._gridDefinitionTemplate[6]/(10.**obj._gridDefinitionTemplate[5])
 261            else:
 262                return earthparams['minor_axis']

 276class ScanModeFlags:
 277    _key = {0:18, 1:18, 10:15, 20:17, 30:17, 31:17, 40:18, 41:18, 90:16, 110:15, 203:18, 204:18, 205:18, 32768:18, 32769:18}

 431class ProjParameters:
 432    def __get__(self, obj, objtype=None):
 433        gdtn = obj._gridDefinitionSection[-1]
 434        if gdtn == 0:
 435            return {'proj':'eqc'}
 436        if gdtn == 10:
 437            return {'proj':'merc','lat_ts':obj.latitudeTrueScale,
 438                    'lon_0':0.5*(obj.longitudeFirstGridpoint+obj.longitudeLastGridpoint)}
 439        elif gdtn == 20:
 440            if obj.projectionCenterFlag == 0:
 441                lat0 = 90.0
 442            elif obj.projectionCenterFlag == 1:
 443                lat0 = -90.0
 444            return {'proj':'stere','lat_ts':obj.latitudeTrueScale,
 445                    'lat_0':lat0,'lon_0':obj.gridOrientation}
 446        elif gdtn == 30:
 447            return {'proj':'lcc','lat_1':obj.standardLatitude1,'lat_2':obj.standardLatitude2,
 448                    'lat_0':obj.latitudeTrueScale,'lon_0':obj.gridOrientation}
 449        elif gdtn == 31:
 450            return {'proj':'aea','lat_1':obj.standardLatitude1,'lat_2':obj.standardLatitude2,
 451                    'lat_0':obj.latitudeTrueScale,'lon_0':obj.gridOrientation}
 452        elif gdtn == 40:
 453            return {'proj':'eqc'}
 454    def __set__(self, obj, value):
 455        pass

10class Grib2Metadata():
11    """
12    Class to hold GRIB2 metadata both as numeric code value as stored in
13    GRIB2 and its plain langauge definition.
14
15    **`value : int`**
16
17    GRIB2 metadata integer code value.
18
19    **`table : str, optional`**
20
21    GRIB2 table to lookup the `value`. Default is None.
22    """
23    __slots__ = ('definition','table','value')
24    def __init__(self, value, table=None):
25        self.value = value
26        self.table = table
27        if self.table is None:
28            self.definition = None
29        else:
30            self.definition = tables.get_value_from_table(self.value,self.table)
31    def __call__(self):
32        return self.value
33    def __repr__(self):
34        return '%s(%d, table = %s)' % (self.__class__.__name__,self.value,self.table)
35    def __str__(self):
36        return '%d - %s' % (self.value,self.definition)
37    def __eq__(self,other):
38        return self.value == other
39    def __gt__(self,other):
40        return self.value > other
41    def __ge__(self,other):
42        return self.value >= other 
43    def __lt__(self,other):
44        return self.value < other
45    def __le__(self,other):
46        return self.value <= other
47    def __contains__(self,other):
48        return other in self.definition

class ProjParameters: 
432class ProjParameters:
433    def __get__(self, obj, objtype=None):
434        gdtn = obj._gridDefinitionSection[-1]
435        if gdtn == 0:
436            return {'proj':'eqc'}
437        if gdtn == 10:
438            return {'proj':'merc','lat_ts':obj.latitudeTrueScale,
439                    'lon_0':0.5*(obj.longitudeFirstGridpoint+obj.longitudeLastGridpoint)}
440        elif gdtn == 20:
441            if obj.projectionCenterFlag == 0:
442                lat0 = 90.0
443            elif obj.projectionCenterFlag == 1:
444                lat0 = -90.0
445            return {'proj':'stere','lat_ts':obj.latitudeTrueScale,
446                    'lat_0':lat0,'lon_0':obj.gridOrientation}
447        elif gdtn == 30:
448            return {'proj':'lcc','lat_1':obj.standardLatitude1,'lat_2':obj.standardLatitude2,
449                    'lat_0':obj.latitudeTrueScale,'lon_0':obj.gridOrientation}
450        elif gdtn == 31:
451            return {'proj':'aea','lat_1':obj.standardLatitude1,'lat_2':obj.standardLatitude2,
452                    'lat_0':obj.latitudeTrueScale,'lon_0':obj.gridOrientation}
453        elif gdtn == 40:
454            return {'proj':'eqc'}
455    def __set__(self, obj, value):
456        pass
